Detailed Description

cvmx_lmc::_fadr

This register only captures the first transaction with ECC errors. A DED error can over-write this register with its failing addresses if the first error was a SEC. If you write LMC()_INT -> SEC_ERR/DED_ERR, it clears the error bits and captures the next failing address. If FDIMM is 1, that means the error is in the high DIMM. LMC()_FADR captures the failing pre-scrambled address location (split into DIMM, bunk, bank, etc). If scrambling is off, then LMC()_FADR will also capture the failing physical location in the DRAM parts. LMC()_SCRAMBLED_FADR captures the actual failing address location in the physical DRAM parts, i.e., * If scrambling is on, LMC()_SCRAMBLED_FADR contains the failing physical location in the DRAM parts (split into DIMM, bunk, bank, etc.) If scrambling is off, the pre-scramble and post-scramble addresses are the same; and so the contents of LMC()_SCRAMBLED_FADR match the contents of LMC()_FADR.
